Rating: 3
This was a great refreshing new taste and we will absolutely do this again. It can be improvised with ingredients on hand. We had found some very nice fresh trout filets to start with. I did not have plum tomatoes on hand but I did use very fresh ripe hot house tomotoes (no canned as the fresh tomatoes are essential to such a dish!). Lacking parsley, I substituted fresh chopped dill weed. I doubled the fresh garlic and added a little chopped garlic from a jar. I used half of a large red onion instead of the pearl onions and also chopped in three small sun dried tomatoes. Finally, I added 1/4 cup roasted chili salsa. I reduced the white wine to 1/2 cup.

